":"public","site_admin":false},"event":"subscribed","commit_id":null,"commit_url":null,"created_at":"2014-09-17T10:36:01Z","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/issues/comments/55910776","html_url":"https://github.com/glfw/glfw/issues/353#issuecomment-55910776","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/issues/353","id":55910776,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU1OTEwNzc2","user":{"login":"tombsar","id":3090978,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMwOTA5Nzg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3090978?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar","html_url":"https://github.com/tombsar","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2014-09-17T15:25:21Z","updated_at":"2014-09-17T15:25:21Z","body":"I have just tried cursoranim with latest master on two Linux computers (both with X11, no trace of Wayland). Results:\n1. CentOS 6.5 with GNOME 2.28, Nvidia GeForce GT 520, NVIDIA drivers (version 340.?). Cursor animates correctly.\n2. Debian 7.6 with IceWM 1.3.7, ATI Radeon HD 3470, Mesa 8.0.5. Cursor becomes a solid white square (as reported by @ricardomv).\n\nHowever...\n\nAs an experiment on computer 2, I tried changing the pixel values written by cursoranim (from transparent white #ffff to transparent red #f00f) and got very strange results. It turns out it is very difficult to accurately screenshot the cursor, so please excuse me taking a photo of the screen.\n\n![img_20140917_161556](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3090978/4306128/66fcc05c-3e7e-11e4-8d5a-898c5cb21128.jpg)\n\nIt seems as though the cursor is being blended with the screen pixels in a strange way, so that the colour of the destination pixel is influencing the blending factor. In particular, a black destination pixel will be overwritten irrespective of the alpha of the cursor image, hence the appearance as a solid square within the client area.\n","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/issues/comments/55910776/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"tombsar","id":3090978,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMwOTA5Nzg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3090978?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar","html_url":"https://github.com/tombsar","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tombsar/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"id":166690704,"node_id":"MDE0Ok1lbnRpb25lZEV2ZW50MTY2NjkwNzA0","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/issues/events/166690704","actor":{"login":"ricardomv","id":3892391,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM4OTIzOTE=","av